"{\"uid\": \"searchenginejournal.com-most-emotionally-engaging-olympic-ads-522942\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Our fith annual State of SEO Report is here!\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 44, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's packed with valuable insights.\", \"from\": 45, \"to\": 80, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Uncover the top factors currently affecting SEO, and what this means for your strategy.\", \"from\": 81, \"to\": 168, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 125, \"end\": 128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Search_engine_optimization\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5746142071812906e-71, \"text\": \"SEO\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Search_engine_optimization\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Search_engine_optimization\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This stack is built for small teams and busy owners who want clarity, shortcuts, and strategies that work.\", \"from\": 170, \"to\": 276, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Reserve your seat to see where your brand stands in the 2026 AI search race.\", \"from\": 278, \"to\": 354, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 339, \"end\": 341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.831760392842409e-16, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PPC Trends is back for its eighth edition, bringing together top industry experts to share field-tested insights on how to stay visible, maintain control, and drive performance in increasingly AI-first ad ecosystems.\", \"from\": 356, \"to\": 572, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 356, \"end\": 359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pay-per-click\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3812796729025072e-18, \"text\": \"PPC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pay-per-click\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pay-per-click\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PPC Trends is back for its eighth edition, bringing together top industry experts to share field-tested insights on how to stay visible, maintain control, and drive performance in increasingly AI-first ad ecosystems.\", \"from\": 574, \"to\": 790, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 574, \"end\": 577, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pay-per-click\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3812796729025072e-18, \"text\": \"PPC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pay-per-click\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pay-per-click\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reserve your seat to see where your brand stands in the 2026 AI search race.\", \"from\": 792, \"to\": 868, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 853, \"end\": 855, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.831760392842409e-16, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Discover the most emotionally engaging Olympics and get inspiration for your video content.\", \"from\": 870, \"to\": 961, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Find out which ads have elicited intense positive emotions.\", \"from\": 962, \"to\": 1021, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With the 2024 Olympic Games in Paris officially opening today, DAIVID used its advanced content testing platform to see which ads from the global sporting event have elicited the most intense positive emotions of all time.\", \"from\": 1023, \"to\": 1245, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1054, \"end\": 1059, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.933279238024697e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Procter & Gamble (P&G) dominates DAIVID's all time chart, with five of the top most emotionally engaging Olympics ads - including the top three tear-jerking positions.\", \"from\": 1247, \"to\": 1414, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1247, \"end\": 1269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Procter & Gamble (P&G)\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, the rest of the search and marketing community will want to figure out what the American multinational consumer goods corporation headquartered in Cincinnati, Ohio has understood for more than a dozen years.\", \"from\": 1416, \"to\": 1627, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1500, \"end\": 1508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999588775578495, \"rank\": 4.095617073377675e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1567, \"end\": 1577, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cincinnati\", \"score\": 0.9999999554265752, \"rank\": 4.450995749683656e-08, \"text\": \"Cincinnati\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cincinnati\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cincinnati\"}, {\"begin\": 1579, \"end\": 1583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ohio\", \"score\": 0.9998883154420192, \"rank\": 9.65567506426106e-05, \"text\": \"Ohio\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ohio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ohio\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although for the Olympic Games in Paris 2024, the consumer products maker announced back in May that it was going to focus its marketing at the Games on its individual brands - including Pampers, Ariel, Fairy, Gillette Venus, Gillette, Always, Head & Shoulders, Oral-B, and ZzzQuil.\", \"from\": 1629, \"to\": 1911, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1663, \"end\": 1673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1947490233934774e-22, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1816, \"end\": 1823, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pampers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pampers\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pampers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pampers\"}, {\"begin\": 1839, \"end\": 1853, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gillette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gillette Venus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gillette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gillette\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, how's that working out?\", \"from\": 1913, \"to\": 1940, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Well, let us just say none of P&G's brands are at the top of the latest chart, according to a new AI rankingby DAIVID.\", \"from\": 1942, \"to\": 2060, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1972, \"end\": 1975, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"P&G\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\"}, {\"begin\": 2040, \"end\": 2042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.831760392842409e-16, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps they might want to return to their tried and tested format that was working and resonating with their core audience.\", \"from\": 2062, \"to\": 2186, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As they say - if it ain't broke\\u2026  In first place, the latest version of the Coca-Cola-owned brand's \\\"Pause is Power\\\" campaign, inspired by Simone Biles's choice to prioritize her mental health by stepping back from competition during the 2021 Tokyo Olympics, reached the top spot by evoking the strongest positive emotions (53.8%).\", \"from\": 2187, \"to\": 2518, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2326, \"end\": 2338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Additionally, it achieved a Creative Effectiveness Score of 6.8 out of 10, which measures effectiveness based on attention, emotions, and memory.\", \"from\": 2519, \"to\": 2664, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In a new press release, Forrester said, \\\"Powerade is a worthy gold medal winner and a powerful reminder for brands of the power of doing something different.\", \"from\": 2666, \"to\": 2823, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2707, \"end\": 2715, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Powerade\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2030393391118872e-25, \"text\": \"Powerade\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Powerade\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Powerade\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While many sports commercials are high-octane and action-packed, with win-at-all-costs messaging, 'The Vault' is a notable departure.\", \"from\": 2824, \"to\": 2957, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2923, \"end\": 2932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trace_Vault\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.588785026342866e-23, \"text\": \"The Vault\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trace_Vault\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trace_Vault\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's much slower-paced, reflective and shows a more human side to sport.\\\"\", \"from\": 2958, \"to\": 3031, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In second place is Coca-Cola celebrating human connection.\", \"from\": 3035, \"to\": 3093, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3054, \"end\": 3063, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.690113595689481e-12, \"text\": \"Coca-Cola\", \"types\": [\"Q2095\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to DAIVID's new AI-powered tool, which employs a model trained on millions of consumer data points to forecast the emotional and business impact of an advertisement, this video ad has a score of 53.6%.\", \"from\": 3094, \"to\": 3305, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In third place is the UK bank NatWest with a score of 52.8%    A P&G 2014 Winter Olympics campaign honoring the crucial support mothers provide to athletes is the most emotionally engaging Olympic ad of all time.\", \"from\": 3309, \"to\": 3521, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3331, \"end\": 3333, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999999999699867, \"rank\": 2.9226226899844867e-11, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This accolade comes from DAIVID, a creative effectiveness platform, which found that the \\\"Pick Them Back Up\\\" campaign evoked the strongest positive emotions among viewers.\", \"from\": 3523, \"to\": 3694, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"P&G Thank You, Mom | Pick Them Back Up | Sochi 2014 Olympic Winter Games\\\" led the chart with 59.6% of viewers responding with intense positive emotions.\", \"from\": 3696, \"to\": 3849, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As the video's description says, \\\"For teaching us that falling only makes us stronger.\", \"from\": 3850, \"to\": 3936, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For giving us the encouragement to try again.\", \"from\": 3937, \"to\": 3982, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thank you, Mom.\\\"\", \"from\": 3983, \"to\": 3999, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Following the (emotional) success from 2014, Thank You, Mom - The Winter Olympics (2018) was close behind in second place with a score of 59.5%.\", \"from\": 4003, \"to\": 4147, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This video guides the viewer through moms supporting their kids with their dreams and through their circumstances - whether it be bias over color, religion, disability, or sexual orientation.\", \"from\": 4149, \"to\": 4340, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"P&G's ad from the London 2012 Olympics took third place, with 58.4% of viewers responding with intense positive emotions.\", \"from\": 4344, \"to\": 4465, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4344, \"end\": 4347, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"P&G\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\"}, {\"begin\": 4362, \"end\": 4382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.911267267064125e-26, \"text\": \"London 2012 Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In this 2012 edition of Procter & Gamble's ad campaign, supportive mothers take their children to practices and help the kids deal with setbacks on their way to becoming successful Olympic athletes.\", \"from\": 4467, \"to\": 4665, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4491, \"end\": 4507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Procter & Gamble\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The UK's National Lottery ad, \\\" National Lottery funded athletes - TV advert Extended Version,\\\" took fourth place with a score of 56.9%.\", \"from\": 4669, \"to\": 4805, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4673, \"end\": 4675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999999999699867, \"rank\": 2.9226226899844867e-11, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 4678, \"end\": 4694, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Lottery_Heritage_Fund\", \"score\": 0.9995617219184918, \"rank\": 0.00043846997632278535, \"text\": \"National Lottery\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Lottery_Heritage_Fund\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Lottery_Heritage_Fund\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was inspired by the story of 800-meter runner Jenny Meadows' mother and showcased how National Lottery funding supports British athletes in achieving their dreams.\", \"from\": 4807, \"to\": 4973, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4856, \"end\": 4869, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Meadows\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jenny Meadows\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Meadows\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Meadows\"}, {\"begin\": 4896, \"end\": 4920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Lottery_Community_Fund\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"National Lottery funding\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Lottery_Community_Fund\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Lottery_Community_Fund\"}, {\"begin\": 4930, \"end\": 4937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999998510184125, \"rank\": 1.489698040388934e-07, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another from P&G's Thank You, Mom series for the Rio 2016 Olympics was placed fifth, with 55.9% of viewers responding with intense positive emotions.\", \"from\": 4977, \"to\": 5126, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4990, \"end\": 4993, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"P&G\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\"}, {\"begin\": 5030, \"end\": 5043, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.113500060469492e-20, \"text\": \"2016 Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In this two-minute commercial, P&G features supportive mothers helping their children persevere through difficult circumstances on their way to becoming Olympic champions.\", \"from\": 5128, \"to\": 5299, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5159, \"end\": 5162, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"P&G\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The brand positions itself as the \\\"Proud sponsor of Moms\\\" and uses the tagline: \\\"It takes someone strong to make someone strong.\", \"from\": 5301, \"to\": 5429, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thank you, Mom.\\\"\", \"from\": 5430, \"to\": 5446, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Channel 4, a British free-to-air public broadcast television channel, took sixth place with its \\\"Superhumans\\\" trailer for the Rio Paralympics 2016.\", \"from\": 5450, \"to\": 5597, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 3-minute video ad got a score of 55.7%.\", \"from\": 5598, \"to\": 5641, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Your Goodness is Your Greatness from P&G took seventh place, with 55.5% of viewers responding with intense positive emotions.\", \"from\": 5645, \"to\": 5770, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5682, \"end\": 5685, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"P&G\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"P&G was founded in 1837 by William Procter and James Gamble.\", \"from\": 5776, \"to\": 5836, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5776, \"end\": 5779, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"P&G\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\"}, {\"begin\": 5803, \"end\": 5818, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Cooper_Procter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2491868038080182e-20, \"text\": \"William Procter\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Cooper_Procter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Cooper_Procter\"}, {\"begin\": 5823, \"end\": 5835, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Gamble_(industrialist)\", \"score\": 0.9858529746524863, \"rank\": 0.014336917562726337, \"text\": \"James Gamble\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Gamble_(industrialist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Gamble_(industrialist)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Do you think this gave them a head start on the rest of the field?\", \"from\": 5837, \"to\": 5903, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In a press release, Ian Forrester, CEO and founder of DAIVID, said:  \\\"When it comes to emotional Olympic campaigns, no brand has ever gone faster, higher or stronger than P&G.\", \"from\": 5905, \"to\": 6080, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The company's incredible tributes to the role mums play in helping to put future Olympic champions on the path to Games glory really tug at the emotional heartstrings and are capable of turning even the most cynical viewers into emotional wrecks.\", \"from\": 6082, \"to\": 6328, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'Pick Them Back Up' is a worthy gold winner, generating some of the most intense feelings of positivity we have ever seen for an ad.\\\"\", \"from\": 6330, \"to\": 6463, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He added, \\\"It's also great to see Channel 4's sensational campaign, 'We are The Superhumans' in the top 6.\", \"from\": 6465, \"to\": 6571, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6499, \"end\": 6508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Channel_4\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6148861439746663e-17, \"text\": \"Channel 4\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Channel_4\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Channel_4\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Generating incredibly intense feelings of inspiration, the ad has played a crucial role in putting the Paralympics firmly in the hearts and minds of viewers all around the world.\\\"\", \"from\": 6572, \"to\": 6751, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What can I add?\", \"from\": 6753, \"to\": 6768, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have known Forrester since September 2012, when he joined the Unruly Group as global insight lead.\", \"from\": 6770, \"to\": 6870, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And I talked with him several times over the next six years about Unruly's Viral Spiral charts, which showed which video ads were among the most shared.\", \"from\": 6871, \"to\": 7023, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6952, \"end\": 6958, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spiral\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8925289882210302e-21, \"text\": \"Spiral\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spiral\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spiral\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, I have learned that Forrester has the kind ofExperience, Expertise, Authoritativeness, and Trustworthiness (E-E-A-T)that not only Google talks about, but skeptical journalists and bloggers value, too.\", \"from\": 7025, \"to\": 7229, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7120, \"end\": 7135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trust_(social_science)\", \"score\": 0.9989539615314192, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Trustworthiness\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trust_(social_science)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trust_(social_science)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's why I have quoted him - along with other video gurus - in articles like \\\"What's The Alternative To Spending $7 Million On A Super Bowl Ad?\\\"\", \"from\": 7231, \"to\": 7377, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"as well as \\\"How To Make A Video Go Viral.\\\"\", \"from\": 7378, \"to\": 7420, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And that's why I have cited DAIVID's critical data and strategic insights in articles like \\\"The Best 5 Super Bowl Ads in 2024 (Brands That Got It Right)\\\" as well as \\\"39 Emotions Digital Marketers Can Use In Advertising.\\\"\", \"from\": 7422, \"to\": 7642, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But if you want to figure out what P&G already understands, then it's worth spending a few moments learning more about DAIVID's methodology.\", \"from\": 7644, \"to\": 7784, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7679, \"end\": 7682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"P&G\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Based in London, DAIVID leverages technologies like facial coding, eye tracking, and computer vision to help advertisers enhance the emotional and business impact of their campaigns.\", \"from\": 7786, \"to\": 7968, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7795, \"end\": 7801, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 5.3803121864097555e-12, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their platform allows marketers to assess and improve ad effectiveness on a large scale using advanced data analysis methods.\", \"from\": 7970, \"to\": 8095, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"DAIVID's study of the most emotionally engaging Olympics ads utilized its Self-Serve solution, trained on millions of consumer data points, to predict the emotional reactions and attention levels ads would generate, along with their potential brand and business impacts.\", \"from\": 8097, \"to\": 8367, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The analysis involved 56 Olympic ads, excluding those from the current Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 8369, \"to\": 8455, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8440, \"end\": 8454, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the Paris Olympics has progressed, all released advertisements were uploaded to DAIVID's platform through its API.\", \"from\": 8457, \"to\": 8574, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8464, \"end\": 8478, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 8570, \"end\": 8573, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/API\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0047183405272669e-13, \"text\": \"API\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/API\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/API\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The platform's predictive AI then evaluated and ranked the ads based on the anticipated strength of positive emotions they would evoke.\", \"from\": 8575, \"to\": 8710, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8601, \"end\": 8603, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.831760392842409e-16, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In total, 47 ads were analyzed in the study.\", \"from\": 8711, \"to\": 8755, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So, watch the 10 ads above and see for yourself what kind of video content triggers intense positive emotions in viewers.\", \"from\": 8757, \"to\": 8878, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You may see something that I might have missed.\", \"from\": 8879, \"to\": 8926, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Past performance is no guarantee of future results as P&G found out after not having a mention at the Paris Olympics, despite having 5 ads in the top 7 of all time.\", \"from\": 8928, \"to\": 9092, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8982, \"end\": 8985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"P&G\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Next time you want to know if your ad creative is working, test it.\", \"from\": 9094, \"to\": 9161, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"P&G take note.\", \"from\": 9162, \"to\": 9176, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9162, \"end\": 9165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"P&G\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I know, talking about testing social videos the way that Madison Avenue once tested TV commercials seems like pie in the sky.\", \"from\": 9178, \"to\": 9303, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Does that guarantee future success?\", \"from\": 9305, \"to\": 9340, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Well, AI can not be creative like humans can.\", \"from\": 9341, \"to\": 9386, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9347, \"end\": 9349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.831760392842409e-16, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, the heart of every great video is still innovative, surprising, human-led creativity.\", \"from\": 9388, \"to\": 9477, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But AI can help advertisers to measure and improve the effectiveness of their content at scale.\", \"from\": 9479, \"to\": 9574, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9483, \"end\": 9485, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.831760392842409e-16, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And that can help the creative teams at iconic brands and their agencies to cross the finish line ahead of their competitors.\", \"from\": 9575, \"to\": 9700, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All data fromDAIVID.\", \"from\": 9702, \"to\": 9722, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"More resources:  Featured Image:Gorodenkoff/Shutterstock  Greg Jarboe is president of SEO-PR, which he co-founded with Jamie O'Donnell in 2003.\", \"from\": 9724, \"to\": 9867, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9768, \"end\": 9780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shutterstock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shutterstock\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shutterstock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shutterstock\"}, {\"begin\": 9787, \"end\": 9793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jarboe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jarboe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jarboe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jarboe\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their digital marketing agency has won ...  Join 75,000+ Digital Leaders.\", \"from\": 9868, \"to\": 9941, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Learn how to connect search, AI, and PPC into one unstoppable strategy.\", \"from\": 9943, \"to\": 10014, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9972, \"end\": 9974, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.831760392842409e-16, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 9980, \"end\": 9983, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pay-per-click\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3812796729025072e-18, \"text\": \"PPC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pay-per-click\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pay-per-click\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Join 75,000+ Digital Leaders.\", \"from\": 10016, \"to\": 10045, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Learn how to connect search, AI, and PPC into one unstoppable strategy.\", \"from\": 10047